Spanish courses at the Keio-SFC emphasise communicative competence, and aim to build a solid and high-level base of language ability through a three-year course structure, within a relatively small-sized class environment. In the Autumn semester, in addition to the new students coming in, we are possible to accept already-existing students who desire to start learning this language. 

Intensive 1 is a course that aims to build basic question-and-answer abilities on topics about yourself, and descriptive abilities of your daily activities, with four classes per week with different instructors, but with common teaching material. In grammatical terms, we will be learning: articles, nouns, and adjectives with their distinctions of gender and number, posessive and indicative expressions, verb conjugations in present, present-perfect, imperatives (and henceforth subjunctive present), reflexive verbs, direct and indirect objective pronouns, among others. The material we use this term in Intensive 1, Viaje al español, is an audiovisual material elaborated in Spain, which introduces you to regions and culture of Spain through TV-drama structure, and enables you to learn Spanish in a concrete communicative context. We emphasise the building of listening and speaking abilities, and the aim of the students is to be able to manage simple conversations at the end of the course.

Spanish is a global language. We hope to work with students who are interested in Spanish-speaking world (Latin America, United States, and Spain), and also who wish to widen and deepen their career possibilities through learning of this language.
